textAfterTable: Eric19 Lapeer, MI August 15, 2006 2:58 AM Post #2623340 How old are your hens? carrjohn Kellyville, OK (Zone 7a) August 15, 2006 12:52 PM Post #2624112 Eric, they range from 1 to 6 years. Several of them will lay their eggs in the same nest but only one will do the setting. The others will start another hidden nest somewhere else. John Eufaula Eatonton, GA (Zone 8b) August 15, 2006 5:02 PM Post #2624878 Carrjohn has anyone started settin this nest yet? carrjohn Kellyville, OK (Zone 7a) August 15, 2006 5:28 PM Post #2624951 No, Eufaula, I went out to check this morning and I guess I have a large black snake, or a king snake. Over half of the eggs are missing without a trace. Has to be a snake because an animal will leave empty shells.
